    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03558.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Boston</name>
                    <date when="1888-05-31" rend="right">May 31<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> 1888</date>
                </dateline>  
                <salute>Dear Mr. Whitman:—</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I send you a little token of my esteem as a birthday present. I am very glad you are
                again <unclear reason="damage" cert="high" resp="#es">able</unclear> to write in
                your old style a little. I hope we may yet have a second volume of Leaves of Grass
                from you if such is compatible with 69 years.</p>
            <p>I wish you many happy returns of this day.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Your friend</salute>
                <signed rend="right">F.S. Ryman</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Will you please let me know if this reaches you safely.</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03558.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#unk">F.S. Ryman</note>
        </body>
    </text>
